// i=2: needs nums[2] > nums[1] (7) and nums[2] > nums[0]. Requires nums[2] >= 8. Cost >= 5.
// If we make i=0 a peak (e.g., nums[0]=8), array is [8, 7, 3].
// Now i=2 peak: 3 > 7 (False). Requires nums[2] >= 8. Array [8, 7, 8].
